1Q.
What is Mutable string in java explain with an example?
Ans.
 Mutable string, we can change the contents of an existing object, which does not create a new object.
 public class mutabe_buffer {
    public static void main(String args[]){
        StringBuffer sBuffer1=new StringBuffer("Welcome");
        System.out.println("Original String is : " + sBuffer1);
        //using append method
        sBuffer1.append(" To Edubca");
        System.out.println("Modified String after append is : " + sBuffer1);
        }
    
}

2Q.
WAP to reverse a string
input : "PWSKILLS"
output : "SLLIKSWP"
public class reverse {
    public static void main(String []args)
    {
        StringBuffer s=new StringBuffer("PWSKILLS");
        s.reverse();
        System.out.println(s);
    }
    
}


3Q.
WAP to reverse a sentence while preserving the position
input : Think Twice
output : knihT eciwT

public class reverse {
    public static void main(String []args)
    {
        StringBuffer s=new StringBuffer("Think Twice");
        s.reverse();
        System.out.println(s);
    }
    
}

4Q.
WAP to sort a String Alphabetically.


import java.util.Arrays;
 
class Alpha {
 
    static void sortString(String str) {
        char []arr = str.toCharArray();
        Arrays.sort(arr);
        System.out.print(String.valueOf(arr));
    }
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String s = "Shahzad";
        sortString(s);
    }
}
